Since last thread went to hell heres my response again.

I like to think of humanity in an anthro world the same way we see humanity in WH40k. On a basic level, we're fairly weak, physically. But due to our intelligence and Adaptatbillity we properspered and became the top species before slowly falling back down. In my setting, humanity learns the fastest and has the greatest brain capacity (bearing a few others). Dragons are technically alot smarter than us but we learn faster. It took the humanity only decades to learn what took dragons centuries. As for the anthros, they're pretty much hunched tribal bipedal animals. Over time humans interbreed with the anthros (similar to Nenatherthal interbreeding with us) and they become like us,(straighter posture, genitals and other body parts resembling the human form, greater brain capacity, etc.) We were able to evolve much further than the anthros did and so we stand out, even against our primate ancestors. Anthros begin to see us the same way we see elves(shiny, almost immortal beings that are wise and make unimaginable tools) In the present of this setting, humanity more or less been reduced to a shell of its former self due to our constant pursuit of knowledge unknowingly leading to our downfall(the specific reason why we fall is up to you) now there aren't many of us left, maybe 1 in 200 or more, anthros now bear certain human traits while still mostly being just a bipedal animal. We are a dying race. And we left all our technology and culture to the anthros. Anthros now live better because of our existence. We are not entirely superior, just somewhat special.
That is what dear humanity did.
